Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Reinforcement Learning is the main focus of the paper, as the authors propose extensions to a model-based ARL method called H-learning. The paper discusses how H-learning can be scaled up to handle large state spaces by approximating the domain models and the value function. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the paper, as the authors propose to represent the action models and reward functions in the form of Bayesian networks. This allows for more efficient learning and inference in domains with large state spaces.
